Dick Blum, a successful businessman and humanitarian, has passed away. He dedicated his public life to fighting poverty globally and was known for his work with the American Himalayan Foundation, which focused on building schools and hospitals in the Tibetan community. He was also a strong supporter of his alma mater, the University of California, where he established the Blum Center for Developing Economies. Beyond his professional accomplishments, Dick was known for his personal decency and generosity, championing human rights and making a difference in the world. His legacy will live on in the families and communities he touched. The writer, who served alongside Dick's wife Senator Dianne Feinstein on the Senate Judiciary Committee, expresses their sadness and offers condolences to Senator Feinstein, their family, and all those who knew and loved Dick Blum.